Today’s Update…
Double Can Release at Both Spots!

All Your Friends - New Zealand IPA w/ Galaxy & Nelson, 7.0% abv
Compared to our West Coast IPA, this one’s a bit lighter in bitterness, with a dab of malty crackeriness, and then hits with two hops from down under that we are absolutely in love with! Hoppy aromatic layers of fresh kiwi, honeydew, passionfruit, and orange marmalade. $16 per 4pack. No limit.
• • • • • • • • •
Cheating Death - California DIPA w/ Strata, Galaxy, & Mosaic, 9.1% abv
Featuring one of our current favorite hops, Strata from @indiehops , we’ve blended in some Galaxy and Mosaic hops as well. Light in body, light in color, with a firm bitterness and hoppy flavors of cotton candy and lychee dominating. $18 per 4pack. No limit.

node.text:
Today’s Update!
Releasing one of our West Coast favs at both spots. Our Online Beer Shop is back open, with a couple pre-sell drops for your weekend needs.
• • • • • • • • •
Radiant Beauty - West Coast IPA w/ Citra, Simcoe & Mosaic, 6.7% abv
Our West Coast IPA that celebrates the love that we have for our beloved mascot, Cheeky! Layered with the holy trinity of hops; Citra, Mosaic, and Simcoe for a radiantly clear IPA. We’ve been lucky enough to win a Silver at the 2018 World Beer Cup and a Silver at the 2019 Great American Beer Festival for this one. $16 per 4pack. No Limit.
• • • • • • • • •
Our Online Beer Shop is back open with the beers in the pic above! Check out greencheekbeer.com to place your order, and we’ll send those goodies straight to your California doorstep! We’ll be shipping these on Thursday, to arrive on Friday. If you want to order Merch (not beer), we ship to most places, even to York!
• • • • • • • • •
You may notice a couple beers in our Online Beer Shop pic above that aren’t available quite yet. This is what other breweries refer to as a “Pre-sell” (insert air quotes if you’re reading out loud), which means that we’re canning those up today and releasing them tomorrow at both spots, but are making them available for the Online Beer Shop so that your weekend could be that much more radical. And by radical, we mean like TOTALLY RADICAL!!!

node.text:
Today’s Update…
Fresh cans and new draft of lager! Also, our Online Beer Shop is back open with the beers above!
• • • • • • • • •
Bier - Helles-Style Lager, 5.2% abv
Using all German ingredients, except for the water, each batch is another baby step towards recreating what we’ve experienced in Munich. Straw in color, with a subtly and nuance that is hard to describe and instead needs to be experienced! Notes of fresh baked bread, herbal tea, and hay create a beer style that is praised for it’s liter-worthy drinkability. $14 per 4pack. No limit.
• • • • • • • • •
Beach Buddy - Light Beer, 4.0% abv
This may not be the buddy you can rely on to scare away the seagulls from your snacks, but it's just a beer, what do you expect?  Our new all-malt lager is a nod to German-style Leightbier, where it’s low in abv, but keeps body and bitterness slightly higher than what you'd expect in an American Light Lager. Best served ice cold with some tasty waves. Draft Only.
• • • • • • • • •
Our Online Beer Shop is back open with the beers in the pic above! Check out greencheekbeer.com to place your order, and we’ll send those goodies straight to your California doorstep! Today’s Update…
Can Release at Both Spots!
• • • • • • • • •
Timbo Pils // Collab w/ @highlandparkbrewery // West Coast Pilsner w/ Mosaic & Citra, 5.8%
Our best pallys over at Highland Park Brewery shared their recipe of their fan favorite Timbo Pils with us, as well as our pals @cellarmakerbrewing , @pinthousebeer , @cloudburstbrew to celebrate their very own Timbo Week! We’ve been huge fans of HPB’s 2019 GABF Gold Medal winner since they’ve been making it and have spent way too much time pondering what kind of wizardry goes into making this delicious wonder.
Timbo starts out as a German Pils in the fermenter, but then after fermentation gets dry hopped heavily with our hand selected lots of Mosaic & Citra hops, to make it into a West Coast Pils. The result is super bright, golden, and hits with hoppy layers of fresh mango, fruit by the foot, and juicy mandarin. $16 per 4pack. No limit

Today’s Update…
Can & Crowler Release at both spots!
• • • • • • • • •
American For Pale - Hoppy Pale Ale w/ Citra, Strata & Mosaic, 5.4% abv
Our 3rd batch of this one brings us to our favorite spot yet! Vibrant and hoppy throughout, with a delicate kiss of malt across its medium body, and showing off hoppy aromatic layers of nectarine skin, fresh strawberries, and Oro Blanco grapefruit. $11 per Crowler (32oz)
• • • • • • • • •
Australian For Pale - Hoppy Pale Ale w/ Motueka, Galaxy & Nelson, 5.8% abv
This super hoppy pale ale gets hit in the boil and the dry hop with some of our favorite Southern Hemisphere hops; Galaxy, Motueka & Nelson. The malt flavor is almost non-existent with the flavor profile only showcasing these hoppy beauties. The lime flavor pops the most, with peach rings and mango trailing behind. 2019 Gold Medal winner at the Great American Beer Festival in the Australian-style Pale Ale category. $15 per 4pack. No limit.

Today’s Update…
Fresh cans and draft of this summertime crusher is back at both spots!
• • • • • • • • •
Here We Are - Belgian-style White Ale w/ California Oranges & Coriander, 5.0% abv
Using Raw Wheat, Pilsner Malt, old fashioned oats, and then fermented with an estery Belgian yeast. We finished it off with fresh ground coriander and house made dried orange peel from locally grown Navel Oranges. The result is a thirst quencher and definitely a reminder to us of how much we love this beer style! The spice and zest are present, but without trampling all over the expressive yeast. $14 per 4pack. No limit.

Fresh cans now at both spots!
• • • • • • • • •
New Adventures // Nitro Golden Milk Stout - Collab w/ @portolacoffee - 5.4% abv
We teamed up with our bud, Jeff Duggan of Portola Coffee, to bring you something that looks like a blonde ale, but tastes like a coffee milk stout! It’s full-bodied, creamy like a Portola cappuccino, and hits with flavors of fresh baked chocolate chip cookies, toasted almonds, and coffee, yep, lots of coffee! Each can is ON NITRO, so you’ll want to give it a light shake for 30 seconds, let it rest for 30 seconds, crack it open, and then pour fast, down the side of your pint glass. *contains lactose* $18 per 4pack. No Limit.

Don’t Wake Me Up - DDH Hazy Triple IPA w/ Citra, Strata & Mosaic. 10.2% abv
Our highest rated beer on @untappd makes its return! Double dry hopped with Citra and then hit with equal parts Mosaic and Strata. Raw wheat and old fashioned oats help create the base, but it’s really all about the hops for this one. Milky yellow in color, with flavorful hoppy layers of passionfruit, guava, and kumquat. $24 per 4pack. Limit 4pp.
